# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Wear Test — product-family language (for domain experts & solution designers)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# WHAT THIS FILE IS
#   A .layer file defines VOCABULARY and STRUCTURE for authoring wear-test
#   products in the IDE. It is not the running app — that lives in
#   wear_test.veil (stock product) and client packages (e.g. brooks_wear_test).
#
# DOMAIN STORY (one paragraph)
#   A retail/brand Tenant runs many wear-test programs. They deploy one
#   Wear Test Application. Inside it, ops create multiple Initiatives
#   (each initiative is one wear-test run). Creating an initiative is guided
#   by a Wizard with five simple steps. Participant lists come from the
#   platform (dlx_core): Cohort, List, Segment, Roster — not reinvented here.
#
# WHO TOUCHES WHAT
#   · Language designers  → this file (wear_test.layer)
#   · Product engineers   → wear_test.veil (default services + domain model)
#   · Client solutions    → brooks_wear_test.veil (extends, does not fork the DSL)
#   · Day-to-day ops      → Dashboard UI (may never open these sources)
#
# HOW TO READ THE GRAPH
#   Select a construct on the canvas → property panel "About" shows the domain
#   description. Palette tiles also show short descriptions.
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

pkg wear_test v1
  desc "Wear testing product-family DSL: Application, Initiative, wizard, dashboard. Built on dlx_core (cohorts, tenants)."
  author "VEIL"
  use ddd

  # ─── Containers: Application & Dashboard ─────────────────────────────────

  construct WearTestApplication
    kw wear_app
    mt mod
    au
    desc "Tenant-scoped product you deploy once. Contains the dashboard and all wear-test Initiatives for that client. Deploying the Application does not create a wear test by itself — ops create Initiatives under it."
    visual
      icon "👟"
      color "#f59e0b"
      label "Wear Test Application"
    in top
    present
      view groups
        label "Layers"
        layout tabs
        members by_source_group
        tabs domain, application, infrastructure, presentation
        default
      view model
        label "Model"
        layout tree
        members by_host_children
        roots Initiative
        nest Enrollment under Initiative when declared_in_parent
        nest SignalBinding under Initiative when declared_in_parent
        nest DataPrep under Initiative when declared_in_parent
        nest Activation under Initiative when declared_in_parent
        nest FeedbackChannel under Initiative when declared_in_parent
        nest Wizard under Initiative when declared_in_parent
        orphan_policy list

  construct WearTestDashboard
    kw wear_dashboard
    mt mod
    desc "Operations home for a Wear Test Application: list initiatives, see status, open the create-initiative wizard, monitor active runs. Not a single wear-test detail page — it governs many initiatives."
    visual
      icon "📊"
      color "#0ea5e9"
      label "Wear Test Dashboard"
    in top

  # ─── Initiative: one wear-test run ───────────────────────────────────────

  construct Initiative
    kw initiative
    mt struct
    desc "One wear-test program instance (one run). A single Tenant/Application may have many Initiatives (e.g. Fall Launch, Winter Waterproof). Holds enrollment, signal bindings, data prep, activations, and feedback configuration."
    visual
      icon "🎯"
      color "#f59e0b"
      label "Initiative"
    in WearTestApplication
    group domain
    present
      role container
      nestable_in model as root

  construct Enrollment
    kw enrollment
    mt struct
    desc "STEP 1 of the wizard — who participates. Options map to dlx_core: entire Cohort, a List, a Segment, a Roster, or Custom rules. Does not store the people themselves; it stores which platform appliance to use."
    visual
      icon "✅"
      color "#10b981"
      label "Enrollment"
    in Initiative
    group domain

  construct SignalBinding
    kw signal_binding
    mt struct
    desc "STEP 2 (part of configure) — which signals this initiative cares about. This is a binding to a signal catalog, not the catalog itself. Open question: signal catalog may later live in platform; binding always lives on the Initiative."
    visual
      icon "📡"
      color "#8b5cf6"
      label "Signal binding"
    in Initiative
    group domain

  construct DataPrep
    kw data_prep
    mt struct
    desc "STEP 3 — prepare data before the test runs. Expert surface stays simple (named inputs and transforms). Implementations can be complex (pipelines, jobs, persistence) while still declared under this construct. Contains InputData and Transform children."
    visual
      icon "🔧"
      color "#64748b"
      label "Data prep"
    in Initiative
    group domain
    has
      InputData[]
      Transform[]

  construct InputData
    kw input_data
    mt struct
    desc "A named input source for data prep (file, query, appliance export, …). Experts name the input; engineers wire how it is loaded."
    visual
      icon "📥"
      color "#94a3b8"
      label "Input data"
    in DataPrep
    group domain

  construct Transform
    kw transform
    mt struct
    desc "A named transformation over input data. May map to generated jobs or ports. This is where heavy programming often lives without abandoning the wear-test language."
    visual
      icon "⚙️"
      color "#78716c"
      label "Transform"
    in DataPrep
    group domain

  construct Activation
    kw activation
    mt struct
    desc "STEP 4 — what the system does when conditions are met (schedules, signal reactions, notifications). Pairs with SignalBinding: bindings say what we listen to; activations say what we fire."
    visual
      icon "⚡"
      color "#eab308"
      label "Activation"
    in Initiative
    group domain

  construct FeedbackChannel
    kw feedback_channel
    mt struct
    desc "STEP 5 — how we collect feedback from participants (survey, in-app prompt, email, …). Configuration only; actual survey products may sit behind adapters later."
    visual
      icon "💬"
      color "#06b6d4"
      label "Feedback channel"
    in Initiative
    group domain

  # ─── Wizard: guided create of an Initiative ──────────────────────────────

  construct Wizard
    kw wizard
    mt struct
    desc "Expert-facing setup flow for a new Initiative. Default stock wizard has five WizardSteps (cohort → configure → data prep → activations → feedback). The UI wizard is generated from this structure; the CreateInitiative service implements it."
    visual
      icon "🧙"
      color "#a855f7"
      label "Wizard"
    in Initiative
    group application
    has
      WizardStep[]

  construct WizardStep
    kw wizard_step
    mt struct
    desc "One step in the create-initiative wizard. Use @step with a key such as 1_cohort, 2_configure, 3_data_prep, 4_activations, or 5_feedback so the UI and services stay aligned."
    visual
      icon "1️⃣"
      color "#c084fc"
      label "Wizard step"
    ann
      step: "Stable key for this step (1_cohort, 2_configure, 3_data_prep, 4_activations, 5_feedback)" value
    in Wizard
    group application

  prompt
    You author wear-test product packages that `use wear_test` and `use dlx_core`.

    ## Domain model (read this first)
    Tenant → Wear Test Application (one deploy) → many Initiatives (each is a wear-test run).
    Dashboard is how ops list and monitor initiatives.
    Wizard creates an Initiative in five simple steps; Step 3 (data prep) may contain deep logic.

    ## Default wizard steps
    1. Enrollment — who participates (cohort / list / segment / roster via dlx_core)
    2. Configure — name, dates, signal bindings
    3. Data prep — input_data + transform (complex work still lives under this shape)
    4. Activations — what fires when
    5. Feedback channels — how we collect feedback

    ## Platform boundary
    - Cohort, List, Segment, Roster, Tenant, User are dlx_core — never redefine them here.
    - Client-specific extras go in a client package (e.g. brooks_wear_test.veil).
    - Prefer initiative / enrollment / signal_binding / data_prep / activation /
      feedback_channel / wizard / wizard_step over ad-hoc names (no "TestPlan").

  present
    role WearTestApplication
      view model
        layout tree
    role Initiative
      view model
        layout tree
